result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: No contact with MML or residence. May have contact while in custody only.

1:32 PM Defendant Seth Maurice Livingston appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Ryan Reid appears with defendant. Attorney Allison Cogbill in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Address updated to 1111 John Avenue Superior. Attorney acknowledges receipt, waives reading, pleads not guilty. Court accepts plea. 
State requests $1500 cash, no contact with MML or residence. On probation at the time of this offense. In warrant status since July, 2022. Cites priors. Victim requesting in custody contact only. 
Attorney Reid asks for signature or low cash bail. Long resident of Douglas County. No FTA's. 
Defendant makes statements. Has made all court appearances.
Court orders $750 cash, with conditions of no contact with MML or her residence. May have contact while in custody only.
Status conference scheduled for December 16, 2022 at 11:30 am.
